      "fact": "Salvatore 'Toto' Schillaci had 1 international cap and 0 goals before the 1990 WC. He came off the bench against Austria, scored, and ended the tournament with 6 goals — winning both the Golden Boot and Player of the Tournament for hosts Italy.",
